assignment has 30 unique elements and is much messier so I’ll start with the assignments with somewhat consistent words in their names. Since some assignments have ‘Git’ and ‘Project Management’ occurring consistently, I’ll use regular expressions to find all the rows with ‘Git’ or ‘Project Management’ and replace them with “Using Git from RStudio” and “Project Management with RStudio”.

.* in regex means match anything, so it’ll match any string as long as it has ‘git’ or ‘project management’. This will be case-insensitive matching.

#'?' matches whether there is a space before git or not
raw_data$assignment %>%
    sub(".* ?git .*", "Using Git from RStudio", ., ignore.case = TRUE) ->
        raw_data$assignment

raw_data$assignment %>%
    sub(".*project management.*", "Project Management with RStudio", .,
        ignore.case = TRUE) -> raw_data$assignment

Getting Ch. 2 and 3 labs and chapter 6 reading is a little more complex. Chaper 3 matches needs two patterns separated by | to match both:

raw_data$assignment %>%
    sub(".*Ch(apter)? ?2.*(assignment|lab).*", "Lab: ISLRv2 Chapter 2", .,
        ignore.case = TRUE) -> raw_data$assignment

Data exploration

Datatable

# get durations
raw_data %>% mutate(duration = as.numeric(end_time - start_time)) -> assignments
DT::datatable(assignments)

Number of assignments done per person

assignments %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = forcats::fct_infreq(ID))) + # forcats::fct_infreq sorts the IDs by count
    geom_bar(stat = "count") +
    xlab("ID") +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, vjust = 0.5))

Time taken per person

# filter for durations > 0 since the duration calc got negatives
nonz_durations <- assignments %>% subset(duration > 0)
nonz_durations %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = reorder(ID, duration), y = duration)) +
    geom_boxplot() +
    geom_jitter(aes(color = assignment)) +
    xlab("ID") +
    theme(legend.position = "bottom",
          axis.text.y = element_text(size = 12)) +
    coord_flip()

To see how the type of assignment affects duration, I’ll add assignment_type and assignment_source columns.

nonz_durations %>%
    mutate(assignment_type =
           case_when(
                     startsWith(assignment, "Reading") ~ "Reading",
                     startsWith(assignment, "Lab") ~ "Lab",
                     grepl("Project Management|Git", assignment) ~ "Reading")) %>%
    mutate(assignment_source =
           case_when(
                     grepl("ISLRv2", assignment) ~ "ISLRv2",
                     grepl("Experimental Design for Biologists", assignment) ~ "EDB",
                     grepl("RStudio", ignore.case = TRUE, assignment) ~ "Software Carpentry")) -> nonz_durations
